# BePlus Smart Search — front-end accessibility

## JavaScript (`admin/js/`, `assets/js/`)

- **Autocomplete:** implement combobox keyboard nav (see [`bpss-a11y-blocks.mdc`](./bpss-a11y-blocks.mdc)); trap focus inside open dropdown only when modal-style overlay is used.
- **Live region:** announce result counts and errors via `aria-live="polite"` — debounce announcements to avoid chatter.
- **Admin React:** form controls need `<label>` or `aria-label`; error messages linked with `aria-describedby`.
- **Reduced motion:** check `window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches` before animating dropdown open/close.

## CSS (`assets/css/`)

- Use **`:focus-visible`**, not bare `:focus`, for interactive elements.
- Add **`@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)`** when adding transitions on dropdown or skeleton loaders.
- Minimum touch target ~44×44px for mobile clear/submit buttons where feasible.

Compile with **`npm run build`** — do not edit `build/**` directly.

```text
❌ .beplus-smart-search__input:focus { outline: none; }
✅ .beplus-smart-search__input:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid currentColor; outline-offset: 2px; }
```
